iv class=3D"max-w-[920px] font-dm-sans"><h2 id=3D"what-is-an-ein" class=3D"=
scroll-mt-28 mt-6 mb-2 text-2xl lg:text-[30px] font-semibold text-black"><s=
trong class=3D"font-semibold">What is an EIN?</strong></h2><p class=3D"mb-4=
 text-base leading-7 text-black sm:text-lg">The Internal Revenue Service (I=
RS) assigns Employer Identification Numbers (EINs), which are distinct nine=
-digit numbers to business entities for taxation purposes. Employers rely h=
eavily on this number, which is formatted as XX-XXXXXXX, as a useful tool f=
or filing taxes.</p><p class=3D"mb-4 text-base leading-7 text-black sm:text=
-lg">An EIN guarantees compliance with federal tax rules and expedites the =
identification procedure for businesses. To operate lawfully in the United =
States, all businesses must obtain an EIN in order to conduct business. By =
taking this action, the federal tax system=E2=80=99s accounting for firms i=
s guaranteed.</p><p class=3D"mb-4 text-base leading-7 text-black sm:text-lg=
">Sometimes, the terms =E2=80=9CTax Identification Number=E2=80=9D (TIN) an=
d =E2=80=9CEIN=E2=80=9D are used interchangeably. TIN, on the other hand, i=
s a more general phrase that includes any identifier that the IRS uses to f=
ollow tax returns. An example of a TIN is the <a href=3D"https://www.signzy=
.com/us/blog/what-is-ssn-in-background-verification/" target=3D"_blank" rel=
=3D"noopener noreferrer" class=3D"text-[#308dff] underline-offset-2 hover:u=
nderline">Social Security Number (SSN)</a>, which is also applicable to ind=
ividuals as opposed to businesses. On the other hand, an EIN is a particula=
r kind of TIN reserved for companies.</p><div class=3D"my-6 rounded-[15px] =
bg-[#e6f0ff] px-6 py-5 flex flex-col gap-3"><p class=3D"m-0 text-[18px] fon=
t-semibold text-black">Related Solutions</p><div class=3D"flex flex-col lg:=
flex-row gap-3 lg:gap-[50px]"><a target=3D"_blank" class=3D"block text-base=
 md:text-lg !text-[#308DFF]" href=3D"https://www.signzy.com/ein-verificatio=
n-api"><span class=3D"text-left text-base md:text-lg !text-[#308DFF]">EIN V=
erification API</span></a><a target=3D"_blank" class=3D"block text-base md:=
text-lg !text-[#308DFF]" href=3D"https://www.signzy.com/business-verificati=
on/ubo-check"><span class=3D"text-left text-base md:text-lg !text-[#308DFF]=
">UBO Check API</span></a><a target=3D"_blank" class=3D"block text-base md:=
text-lg !text-[#308DFF]" href=3D"https://www.signzy.com/use-cases/know-your=
-business"><span class=3D"text-left text-base md:text-lg !text-[#308DFF]">B=
usiness Verification API</span></a></div></div><h2 id=3D"why-do-companies-n=
eed-to-verify-a-businesss-ein-number" class=3D"scroll-mt-28 mt-6 mb-2 text-=
2xl lg:text-[30px] font-semibold text-black"><strong class=3D"font-semibold=
">Why do companies need to verify a business=E2=80=99s EIN number?</strong>=
</h2><p class=3D"mb-4 text-base leading-7 text-black sm:text-lg">When onboa=
rding a new company as a client or partner, businesses in various sectors a=
re required to follow <a href=3D"https://www.signzy.com/us/blog/how-to-veri=
fy-a-business-kyb-process/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer" c=
lass=3D"text-[#308dff] underline-offset-2 hover:underline">=E2=80=9CKnow Yo=
ur Business=E2=80=9D (KYB)</a> processes. In this step, the legality of the=
 company and its proprietors are confirmed, and any possible hazards relate=
d to the partnership are evaluated.</p><p class=3D"mb-4 text-base leading-7=
 text-black sm:text-lg">A valid EIN is necessary for a business operating i=
n the United States to conduct certain financial and insurance-related oper=
ations as well as for lawful operation. As a result, proving the identifica=
tion of the company requires first confirming the EIN.</p><p class=3D"mb-4 =
text-base leading-7 text-black sm:text-lg">Making sure the EIN is legitimat=
e and accurately linked to the firm in question is part of this process. In=
 order to minimize potential hazards and legal responsibilities, the compan=
y might want to reevaluate the collaboration if the EINs do not match.</p><=
h2 id=3D"how-to-verify-an-ein-number-for-a-business" class=3D"scroll-mt-28 =
mt-6 mb-2 text-2xl lg:text-[30px] font-semibold text-black"><strong class=
=3D"font-semibold">How to Verify an EIN number for a business?</strong></h2=
><figure class=3D"my-4"><img src=3D"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/blrzl70g/p=
roduction/47ed49cee80b85e9e7f1805e0201586052cd712d-10041x11160.png" alt=3D"=
tools-to-verify-an-ein-number-image-10" class=3D"h-auto w-full rounded-[10p=
x] object-cover"></figure><h3 class=3D"scroll-mt-28 mt-6 mb-5 text-[24px] f=
ont-semibold text-black">1. IRS Website</h3><p class=3D"mb-4 text-base lead=
ing-7 text-black sm:text-lg">An important and reliable source for free EIN =
numbers is the Internal Revenue Service (IRS). The IRS offers a specific pa=
ge on its official website where anyone may look up an organization=E2=80=
